For all you people who put down the poor girl, give her a break. Yeah, she should of know n better, but did you ever stop to think that maybe she didnt? Who knows she might of not been taught better. Or even if she had, that doesnt make her a terrible person. Now if she were to abandon that child or not take care of its needs properly, then sure put her down, but what people need to do today is start supporting kids when they screw up and help them realize what they done was wrong, and then if they repeat that mistake then take a more harsh action to that person. But make sure they know that someone is willing to help
